    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>/authors/admin/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/authors/admin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Soyoung Choi is a Ph.D. candidate in Nursing at the Pennsylvania State University. Her research topics involve (1) self-care and family caregiving in heart failure, and (2) using digital healthcare technologies (e.g., mobile apps and accessible websites) for improving health-related quality of life of people with visual impairments. To generate scientific knowledge from a large amount of data or big data, she is always self-training herself to be a nurse data scientist. The title of her doctoral dissertation is &amp;ldquo;Exploring the End-of-Life Caregiving Experiences of Family Members of Patients with Advanced Heart Failure: Using a Content Analysis and Text Mining.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
